The paper deals with the problem of text to video moment retrieval, which involves understanding the semantic relationship between natural language queries and video content. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves learning from weak labels, which is a common problem in machine learning and can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The use of attention mechanisms and embeddings also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
